history.content: If you still want the class, no. It just automatically send you these emails to remind you that you are on the waitlist.

You remain on the wait list for the following class:

Term: 2019 Fall

Class: COMPSCI   170 

Section: 001

Reason: Available seats are reserved and you do not meet any requirements for the reserved seats.

You will remain on the wait list until a seat for which you qualify opens.

You are responsible for dropping yourself from the waitlist if you do not wish to enroll in the requested class. You are responsible for any deadlines to drop yourself from the waitlist or the class if you are enrolled in a future date.

Add/Drop Deadlines can be found in the URL below:

https://registrar.berkeley.edu/registration/enrollment

Actions you can take: Please check the class description for a list of reserved seat requirements, contact the department offering the class, or select a different class.

Seat reservations are available at: http://classes.berkeley.edu/
